'''Uḍḍīyana Bandha''' ([[Sanskrit]]) is the abdominal [[Bandha (Yoga)|bandha]] described and employed in [[hatha yoga]]. It involves, after having exhaled all the air out, pulling the abdomen under the rib cage by taking a false inhale while holding the breath and then release the abdomen after a pause. The process is repeated many times before letting the air into the lungs, resuming normal breath.{{cn|date=March 2015}}

